				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-10983633#post-4653892</guid>
				<title>Safety protocols for ordering products from Avelar.</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-10983633/scp-4510#post-4653892</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Tue, 19 May 2020 15:55:06 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>Amozabael</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>3743350</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>Delivery spot designated the &quot;Drop Zone&quot; must be a 1 square km impact resistent landing platform on the ground.<br /> Buildings and structures must be 20&#160;km away from the drop zone.</p> <p>When placing your order, specify the address as the exact coordinates of the drop zone.<br /> When the checkout page is reached, flashing lights and alarm bells will activate at the drop zone.<br /> Before confirming the order, ensure all personnel and objects are 1&#160;km clear of the drop zone.<br /> Once the drop zone is clear, confirm the order.<br /> Wait for the delivery of the package to arrive. DANGER! DO NOT ENTER THE DROP ZONE UNTIL THE PACKAGE ARRIVES!<br /> Once the delivery plane has left, the alarm will stop. Keep clear until then.<br /> After the alarm stops, it is safe to enter the drop zone and retrieve the package.</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
